title: Lowest CO2 Emissions from Energy Fugitive Sources
description: In 2023, the Bahamas recorded one of the lowest carbon dioxide emissions from fugitive emissions in the energy sector, with only 0.0001 Mt CO2e.

title: High Protection Against Tetanus in Newborns
description: In 2023, 100% of newborns in the Bahamas were protected against tetanus, showcasing excellent healthcare coverage for infants.

title: High Female Labor Force Participation
description: In 2023, the labor force participation rate for females aged 15-24 in the Bahamas was 97.935%, indicating strong female engagement in the workforce.

title: High Tariff Rates on Manufactured Products
description: In 2022, the Bahamas had a high tariff rate of 33.23% on manufactured products for most favored nations, indicating significant trade protectionism.
